  "prompt": "What is a word or name for pet lovers, especially dogs?",
  "response": "A common term for people who love pets, especially dogs, is \"dog lovers\" or \"canophiles.\" The word \"canophile\" is derived from the Greek words \"canis,\" meaning dog, and \"phile,\" meaning lover or friend. Another term that is sometimes used is \"cynophile,\" which also comes from Greek, with \"cyno\" meaning dog. \n\nFor a more general term that encompasses lovers of all kinds of pets, \"petophile\" or \"zoophile\" could be used, though the latter can sometimes have negative connotations due to its association with certain inappropriate behaviors. A more commonly accepted general term would be \"animal lover\" or \"pet lover.\"",
